messages.message:
This is actually not a bug -- the backend doesn't generate confidence score yet for longer documents. But I do think we can tweak the text -- this might not always be the reason why a confidence score is unavailable, so showing it as a reason always is misleading. Probably just "model confidence is not available for this field" is enough. cc @Eric Han
@Lee, we purposely distinguish model giving low confidence vs a model can't provide a confidence score to avoid the case that the value is correct but model can't return a score yet. The score is mostly used later for autovalidation in human review -- to you, what makes sense here? from the eng side the 2 scenarios are different, but want to get your view on what the user sees

If we mark all "unknown" as 0% it might generate a lot of noise.
